NAME
    ttytype(4)		- mapping from terminal ports to type

SYNOPSIS
    /etc/ttytype

DESCRIPTION
    This file contains one line for each terminal port.
    The format is: device type, a space and then the port
    name (without the "/dev/" prefix), for example:

	minix tty0
	vt100 tty1

    The tset(1) command uses this file to map a port
    name into the appropriate default device descriptor.

SEE ALSO
    tset(1), ttys(4)
